Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Established in 1991, Option 1 Staffing Services, Inc., assists client organizations in California's Bay Area by finding the candidates best suited to their needs. Leveraging experience serving businesses in fields ranging from accounting and finance to healthcare and information technology, the company applies its Perfect Placement Methodology to the solution of unique staffing challenges. This methodology includes five phases, the first of which centers on an analysis that helps Option 1 Staffing develop a thorough understanding of client needs. Subsequent phases include recruitment, evaluation, selection, and a 100 percent satisfaction guarantee.  Presently, Option 1 Staffing assists nearly 25,000 employment candidates with skills applicable to many fields. The company attracts candidates by delivering the support necessary to find the right position in today's competitive marketplace. That support includes an extensive professional network, through which job candidates encounter career opportunities, as well as consultations with the company’s team of placement experts. Interested candidates can search job opportunities online at Option1Staffing.com or contact an Option 1 Staffing recruiter at (650) 941-5115.  Pursuant to its environmentally friendly values, Option 1 Staffing limits its impact on the natural world by relying more on electronic administration and less on paper, buying supplies from green vendors and encouraging its staff to utilize public transportation and carpooling.  A community minded organization, Option 1 Staffing is helps Heald College students enter the workforce by participating in campus career events. The company also participates in the Career Closets clothing drive, which supports women re-entering the workplace. A company engaged with its broader professional community, Option 1 belongs to the American Staffing Association, an organization dedicated to ethical staffing services, in addition to the California Staffing Professionals, the National Association Women's Business Owners and the Los Altos Chamber of Commerce.

Description: SpareTime offers a platform that enables its users to browse, find, create, and promote community events they can volunteer for.
Full Description: As co-founders of Seeds That Feed, a project aimed at fighting food insecurity in Northwest Arkansas, we were able to take $50 in seed funding, and within 6 months, collect and distribute over 15,000 pounds of fresh produce to local food pantries and community meal programs. The ability to spread awareness, engage volunteers, and attract resources is now imperative to our project’s growth. Seeds that Feed now stands face to face with the need for SpareTime.  There are lots of organizations and projects needing help but many face barriers to engagement and lack visibility. SpareTime is an engagement platform for advancing social good that provides organizations with a way to market their projects to the newest generation of volunteers and donors. Additionally, organizations will be able to sponsor project ideas from the community and/or connect and collaborate with organizations with similar social initiatives. Within SpareTime, users can... - browse the local landscape of community projects - create and generate project ideas for the community* - volunteer and connect with projects based on availability and interests - spread awareness about projects and causes through shares and tweets - fund projects sponsored by one or more accredited organizations - track and grow your community influence and economic impact - view and personalize the first ever living history of your community involvement * A portion of our revenue will be used to promote and support youth led project initiatives through SpareTime for Schools. This is the only platform where users can track and personalize a central record of projects they have supported by adding journal entries and photos. Furthermore, all centralized records are validated and reported by accredited organizations and can serve as a reference for secondary education applications and resumes. Lastly, foundations and private donors will have an opportunity to support their communities by funding newly created and sponsored projects. The project based funding approach will provide the most transparent way for donors to see, monitor, and track the direct impact of their charitable contributions. Many hats... In 2005, while working together at a local restaurant and attending the Walton College of Business, we began our partnership working side by side in a competitive environment. During this time, not only did we find a way to work collaboratively for both of our best interests, but we also laid the foundation of trust that has sustained us since. Our friendship continued to be cultivated because of our common interests, passions, and drive to make a difference.  Beginning again in 2009, our working relationship was rekindled upon the idea of SpareTime and our partnership was formed. While working full time jobs and further developing our concept for SpareTime, we launched Seeds that Feed and continue to watch it grow beyond our wildest expectations! Aron Shelton is the Architect and Visionary of SpareTime--generator of new ideas, surveyor of the competitive landscape, and researcher who shapes and defines our position in the marketplace. Alyssa Snyder is the Director and Marketer behind SpareTime--business and customer developer, scaler and analyzer of new ideas, organizer and strategic planner, and protector of our concept and user experience.

Description: Galerie Michael specializes in fine European paintings, drawings and prints from the 17th century to the present.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: About Galerie Michael            	 Galerie Michael is an exclusive fine art gallery in Beverly Hills, CA. Located on the famed Rodeo Drive, the gallery has been distinguishing itself as a leader in European fine art for more than 30 years.   Specializing in fine European works from the 17th century to the present, Galerie Michael has made a name for itself as one of the leading galleries in the world to locate paintings, drawings and prints from this genre.   The gallery staff works hard to cultivate and maintain relationships with master artist families. In fact, Galerie Michael currently has exclusive rights to represent and exhibit the works of Alexandre Renoir ─ great-grandson of the legendary Auguste Renoir. The gallery has long-term relationships with the families of Cezanne, Pissarro and Mourlot. Additionally, staff also has ties to the printers of legendary artists Picasso, the Modern Masters and Miro.   Client Philosophy At Galerie Michael, clients receive personalized attention from a staff that truly enjoys helping them create a museum quality collection. All clients have unlimited access to the curatorial knowledge, market know-how, planning proficiencies of their staff of fine art scholars. Collections are built to be distinguished, focusing on the up 25 percent of the artists’ oeuvre ─ ensuring clients purchase a piece that will only grow in value.   Nearly 7,500 collectors work with Galerie Michael to find the right European painting, drawing or print. In fact, many of them have been loyal clients since the opening of the gallery more than 30 years ago.   Services Offered As the leading experts on European fine art, Galerie Michael is pleased to offer clients a variety of services, to make their collecting experience pleasant and stress-free. When working with the gallery, clients enjoy: *Customized museum quality framing *Professional grade packaging and shipping to anywhere in the world *Personal art consultant to serve as a trusted advisor throughout the acquisition process *More than 65 years of fine art expertise *Two-year exchange privilege on all works, allowing clients to purchase with ease *Invitations to exclusive lectures by renowned art experts *Complimentary parking and private gallery entrance *Exclusive access to a million dollar art library *Certificate of Authenticity provided with each piece *Access to unlimited resources to search worldwide for specific pieces   Exhibitions and Events Galerie Michael regularly opens its doors to artists and collectors willing to put their works on display. At least 18 annual events are sponsored by the gallery, varying from actions to exclusive exhibitions ─ but always include rare and unique pieces to assist clients in building a unique and valuable collection.   In the past, Galerie Michael has curated Los Angeles area art exhibitions at the Norton Simon Museum, LACMA and the J. Paul Getty Museum. Additionally, members of the gallery’s talented staff are frequently asked to create exhibitions for both nationally and internationally renowned museums. Clients and interested parties are encouraged to frequently check the Galerie Michael website for information on the latest showcase.
